North Korea withdrew from the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty and is in a standoff with six other nations.
North Korea's position is that nuclear weapons are needed for their defense.
The negotiations with South Korea, Japan, China, Russia, the UK and the US to persuade North Korea to cease its nuclear weapons programs are continuing without much progress.
North Korea demands to be treated as a nuclear power and for disarmament talks to apply to all countries involved.
South Korea has proposed that the international community aid North Korea economically and institute a rehabilitation program once the nuclear issue is resolved.
